# Quality Gates -- {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Every change must pass through these 4 gates before reaching production.
> Gates are cumulative -- Gate 2 includes everything from Gate 1.

---

## Gate 1: Pre-Commit

**When:** Before every `git commit`
**Enforced by:** Pre-commit hooks (husky/lint-staged or equivalent)

| Check | Command | Must Pass |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| Lint | `{{LINT_CMD}}` | Zero errors (warnings OK during Phase 0) |
| Type check | `{{TYPE_CHECK_CMD}}` | Zero errors |
| No `console.log` | grep / lint rule | No console.log in committed code |
| No `any` types | `{{TYPE_CHECK_CMD}}` / lint rule | No explicit `any` in new code |
| Import order | lint rule / auto-fix | Sorted and grouped |
| File naming | convention check | kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components |

### Pre-Commit Bypass (Emergency Only)
```bash
git commit --no-verify -m "hotfix: [description]"
```
> Must be followed up with a clean commit within 24 hours.

---

## Gate 2: Pre-PR

**When:** Before opening a pull request
**Enforced by:** CI pipeline ({{CI_PROVIDER}})

| Check | Command | Threshold |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| All Gate 1 checks | (re-run in CI) | Must pass |
| Unit tests | `{{TEST_CMD}}` | 100% pass rate |
| Build succeeds | `{{BUILD_CMD}}` | Zero errors |
| Test coverage | `{{TEST_CMD}} --coverage` | >= {{COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}% on changed files |
| Bundle size | build output check | No increase > {{BUNDLE_SIZE_LIMIT}} |
| No secrets | secret scanner | Zero findings |

### PR Checklist (copy into PR description)
```markdown
- [ ] Gate 1 passes locally
- [ ] Tests added/updated for changed code
- [ ] Build succeeds with no warnings
- [ ] Coverage meets threshold on changed files
- [ ] No hardcoded URLs, secrets, or API keys
- [ ] Tested manually in browser (if UI change)
```

---

## Gate 3: Pre-Merge

**When:** Before merging PR into {{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}
**Enforced by:** Required reviewers + branch protection

| Check | Who | Criteria |
|-------|-----|----------|
| Code review | At least {{REQUIRED_REVIEWERS}} reviewer(s) | Approved with no open threads |
| API contracts | Reviewer | If endpoints changed, OpenAPI/Swagger updated |
| Database schema | Reviewer | If schema changed, migration file included |
| Service hub | Author | Service hub file updated if status changed |
| STATUS.md | Author | Task status updated to "In Review" or "Done" |
| CHANGELOG.md | Author | Session entry appended |

### Merge Strategy
- **Squash merge** for feature branches (clean history)
- **Merge commit** for release branches (preserve branch context)

---

## Gate 4: Pre-Release

**When:** Before deploying to staging/production
**Enforced by:** Release checklist + manual sign-off

| Check | Command / Process | Threshold |
|-------|-------------------|-----------|
| E2E tests | `{{E2E_CMD}}` | 100% pass on critical paths |
| Accessibility | axe/Lighthouse audit | Zero critical violations |
| Performance | Lighthouse CI | Performance >= {{PERF_SCORE_TARGET}} |
| Mobile responsive | Manual check | Key screens render on 375px+ |
| Cross-browser | Manual check | {{SUPPORTED_BROWSERS}} |
| Data migration | If applicable | Rollback plan documented |
| Rollback plan | Document | Documented and tested |

### Release Sign-Off
```
- [ ] All Gate 1-3 checks pass
- [ ] E2E suite green on staging
- [ ] Accessibility audit clean
- [ ] Performance targets met
- [ ] Stakeholder demo completed
- [ ] Rollback procedure verified
- Approved by: _____________ Date: _____________
```
